9.5 Understanding CPU load	

in order to service a task, the kernel provides a runqueue. The kernel adds all tasks to the runqueue, and the scheduler then determines where the task is run. I.E, what core

the command that is useful here is uptime. Uptime shows the live time and also the load average. the output is show in 1, 5, and 15 minute averages. The average is the amount of runnable processes that are waiting in the load queue

use watch uptime to keep a refreshing tally of the cpu load and uptime